.TH GETUSERSHELL 3  2013-06-21 "GNU" "Linux Programmerz Manual"
.SH NAME
getusershell, setusershell, endusershell \- git permitted user shells
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <unistd.h>
.sp
.B char *getusershell(void);
.sp
.B void setusershell(void);
.sp
.B void endusershell(void);
.fi
.sp
.in -4n
Feature Test Macro Requirements fo' glibc (see
.BR feature_test_macros (7)):
.in
.sp
.ad l
.BR getusershell (),
.BR setusershell (),
.BR endusershell ():
.RS 4
_BSD_SOURCE || (_XOPEN_SOURCE && _XOPEN_SOURCE\ <\ 500)
.RE
.ad b
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.BR getusershell ()
function returns tha next line from tha file
.IR /etc/shells ,
openin tha file if necessary.
Da line should contain
the pathname of a valid user shell.
If
.I /etc/shells
does not exist or
is unreadable,
.BR getusershell ()
behaves as if
.I /bin/sh
and
.I /bin/csh
were listed up in tha file.
.PP
The
.BR setusershell ()
function rewinds
.IR /etc/shells .
.PP
The
.BR endusershell ()
function closes
.IR /etc/shells .
.SH RETURN VALUE
The
.BR getusershell ()
function returns a NULL pointa on end-of-file.
.SH FILES
.nf
/etc/shells
.fi
.SH ATTRIBUTES
.SS Multithreadin (see pthreads(7))
The
.BR getusershell (),
.BR setusershell ()
and
.BR endusershell ()
functions is not thread-safe.
